==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sincerity
<hw>Sin*cer"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>sinceritas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>sinc⟦eacute⟧rit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The quality or state of being sincere; honesty of mind or
intention; freedom from simulation, hypocrisy, disguise, or false
pretense; sincereness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I protest, in the <qex>sincerity</qex> of love.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sincerity</qex> is a duty no less plain than important.</q>
<rj><qau>Knox.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sinch</ent>⟦br⟧
